# Metric Resource: HardMatch
<https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/HardMatch> a dqv:Metric ;

    dcterms:identifier "https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/HardMatch" ;
    dcterms:title "Exact lexical string comparison"@en ;
    rdfs:label "HardMatch: Exact lexical string comparison"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "hard_match"^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:version "0.0.1"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
    dcat:landingPage <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/HardMatch> ;

    # Descriptive Content
    dcterms:description """
This metric aims to evaluate whether a generated label exactly matches any existing label in the gold-standard ontology. If the generated label matches a gold label (case-sensitive, character-for-character), the result is 1; otherwise it is strictly 0.

**Example:**

Generate_Label_1: Wine

Generate_Label_2: wine

Generate_Label_3: Liquor

Gold_Standard_Label: Wine

Result:

1. HardMatch(Generate_Label_1, Gold_Standard_Label) = 1
2. HardMatch(Generate_Label_2, Gold_Standard_Label) = 0
3. HardMatch(Generate_Label_3, Gold_Standard_Label) = 0

**What is being measured?**

This metric strictly compares the generated label to the gold-standard labels at the string level. It is the strictest matching approach with zero tolerance for variation and no semantic component.
""" ;
    dcat:keyword "Ontology Concept Matching"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Metric"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Classes"@en ;

    # Relationships and Provenance
    dpv:isApplicableFor <https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q184754> ;
    ftr:hasBenchmark <https://w3id.org/cq2onto/benchmark/ALL> ;
    sio:SIO_000234 <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/HardMatch> ;
    ftr:supportedBy <https://w3id.org/cq2onto/> ;
    dqv:inDimension "Ontology Engineering"^^xsd:string ;

    # Provenance
    dcterms:creator <https://orcid.org/0009-0001-9475-8159> ;
